headline: Doordash forecasts strong quarter on resilient delivery demand
summary: Doordash forecast third-quarter gross merchandise value above Wall Street expectations after topping estimates on Wednesday, betting on robust demand for food and grocery deliveries through its platform. The company's offers and promotions, particularly in its U.S. and international markets for members, has attracted budget-conscious consumers seeking value to its online services. Doordash expects gross merchandise value, a measure of the total dollar value of orders placed through its platform, to be between $24.2 billion and $24.7 billion for the current quarter, above estimates of $23.73 billion, according to estimates compiled by LSEG.
